            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "If you’ve seen the BMW Z8 in person, you know photos don’t do this drop-dead gorgeous car justice. It’s one of the most beautiful cars ever made, especially in this century, drawing heavily on design themes from the 1950s and 1960s. No surprise, Henrik Fisker was the man who penned the design back in middle of the 1990s, although the Z8 didn’t release until 2001.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2020/06/Motorious--8.jpg",
        "caption": "Photo credit: YouTube"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Under that aluminum body was the same 4.9-liter S62 V8 used in the E39 M5. While that was pretty hot, when Alpina got its hands on the Z8 it swapped in a 4.8-liter M62 V8, dropping horsepower slightly and increasing torque.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "BMW Z8 production was capped at 5,703, while the Alpina Z8s were limited to just 555 units. In other words, someone took an incredibly rare collector’s car for a joy ride, then either because they can’t drive worth squat or are a vengeful jerk, they crashed it into a pole.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
